(firstQuint)Platelet-rich-plasma Treating Tennis Elbow.

 Patients with chronic plantar fasciitis will be allocated randomly to have a steroid injection or an autologous platelet concentrate injections.

 Data will be collected before the procedure, 4, 8, 12, 26 weeks and 1 year after the procedure.

 The main outcome measures of this study are pain and function measured with questionnaires.

